been <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/25/24205904/google-pixel-9-leak-marketing-materials\">no shortage of Pixel 9 leaks</a> over the past couple of days, a new ad for the device seems to have leaked in full \u2014 and it shows off a new feature that makes sure you aren\u2019t left out of a group photo.</p>\n<p id=\"N6976y\">The feature, seemingly called \u201cAdd Me,\u201d appears in a leaked ad <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=37&amp;v=pzWA7haE-Sk&amp;embeds_referring_euri=https%3A%2F%2F9to5google.com%2F&amp;source_ve_path=MjM4NTE\">shared with <em>Android Headlines</em></a> by OnLeaks. The ad s", "id": 936567, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206969/google-pixel-9-add-me-group-photos-leak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Pixel 9\u2019s \u2018Add Me\u2019 feature puts you in a group photo even when you\u2019re not there", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T16:31:32+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector collage of the X logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tVzyqGI650oGqlcD9aieQu-SAd0=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73484164/STK160_X_TWITTER_2__C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hNclWF\">X uses your data to train its Grok AI assistant, but if you\u2019d like to opt out of that, you can do that right from your settings menu. It <a href=\"https://x.com/settings/grok_settings\">is accessible on the web right here</a>, or you can find it yourself if you click the three dots menu, then \u201cSettings and privacy,\u201d then \u201cPrivacy and safety,\u201d and then \u201cGrok.\u201d </p>\n<p id=\"qBCbAS\">X\u2019s @Safety account <a href=\"https://x.com/Safety/status/1816874083721838921\">wrote in a post on Friday</a> that the setting is available to all users on the web now and \u201cwill soon be rolled out on mobile.\u201d</p>\n<div id=\"rihChT\">\n<blockquote align=\"center\" class=\"twitter-tweet\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">All X users h", "id": 936069, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206904/x-grok-ai-train-turn-off", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Here\u2019s how to stop X from using your posts to train its AI", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T15:54:25+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/etU1jhSdjPnsOws1Ax0h5uTFtgE=/0x0:1200x800/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73484056/intel_13900k_tomwarren__2_.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>An Intel Core i9-13900K CPU, one of the first types that was identified to sometimes crash games this way.</em> | Photo by Tom Warren / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"f5sLH6\">On Monday, it initially seemed like the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/22/24203959/intel-core-13th-14th-gen-cpu-crash-update-patch\">beginning of the end for Intel\u2019s desktop CPU instability woes</a> \u2014 the company confirmed a patch is coming in mid-August that should address the \u201croot cause\u201d of exposure to elevated voltage. But if your 13th or 14th Gen Intel Core processor is already crashing, that patch apparently won\u2019t fix it. </p>\n<p id=\"aaBAg6\">Citing unnamed sources,<em> </em><a href=\"https://www.tomshardware.com/pc-components/cpus/intel-finally-announces-a-sol", "id": 936070, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206529/intel-13th-14th-gen-crashing-instability-cpu-voltage-q-a", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "There is no fix for Intel\u2019s crashing 13th and 14th Gen CPUs \u2014 any damage is permanent", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T14:37:40+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Samsung Galaxy S24 and S24 Plus side by side showing screen size difference.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/PjCJtpB5M5eUj03jrOyJySrCj4w=/0x0:6000x4000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483919/DSC06601.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Allison Johnson / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yy7rKC\">Samsung\u2019s upcoming One UI 7 update could bring some pretty big changes to the look of its Galaxy devices. Leaked screenshots <a href=\"https://x.com/chunvn8888/status/1816696317558632822\">@chunvn8888</a> shared <a href=\"https://www.smartprix.com/bytes/samsung-one-ui-7-first-look-and-key-features-revealed/\">with <em>Smartprix</em></a> show Samsung\u2019s Android skin with tweaks to the quick settings and notification panels, along with UI elements that take on a rounder appearance throughout.</p>\n<p id=\"VsQaMx\">As shown in the leaked screenshots, it looks like Samsung may split the notification panel from the quick setting shade. The", "id": 935540, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206755/samsung-galaxy-one-ui-7-revealed-leak", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Samsung\u2019s overhauled One UI 7 revealed", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T14:20:29+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Mexico v Canada - International Friendly\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/F8hbxMmLc4ox-hRdRYtdWvIjMQg=/63x0:4563x3000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483868/2156400385.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Bev Priestman, head coach of the Canadian Olympic women\u2019s soccer team, has been suspended for the rest of the Paris Games.</em> | Photo by Vaughn Ridley / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"3akYN8\">The plot in Canadian soccer\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/24/24205155/drones-olympics-soccer-canada-spying\">Olympic drone spying scandal</a> thickens. A <a href=\"https://www.tsn.ca/soccer/canada-s-men-s-and-women-s-soccer-teams-have-relied-on-drones-and-spying-for-years-sources-say-1.2153674\"><em>TSN</em> report</a> alleges that the Canadian men\u2019s and women\u2019s soccer teams have been spying on opponents \u2014 with and without drones \u2014 for years.</p>\n<p id=\"BtMRtz\">Earlier this week, the Canadian Olympic women\u2019s soccer t", "id": 935113, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206788/canada-soccer-drones-spying-olympics", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Canadian soccer teams have been spying with drones for years", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T13:57:55+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A black plastic car charging mount with the ESR logo at the center of the circular charging puck is mounted to a car\u2019s vent.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Ut_Yq5AE6kJvvu6sX4bd_vAvuMc=/0x163:3910x2770/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483758/IMG_1743.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>If you\u2019re using a newer iPhone, ESR\u2019s latest car mount is just as fast as an official MagSafe charger.</em> | Photo by Thomas Ricker / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Ktqzxb\">At this point, I can confidently say that the new Qi2 wireless standard has found its footing. Everyone from <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24027019/anker-qi2-hands-on-magsafe-speed\">Anker</a> to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/29/24054150/nomad-stand-qi2-price-release-date-specs-details-15w-fast-charging-magsafe-iphone-15\">Nomad</a> now offers a selection of speedy Qi2 chargers, with the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/18/24200797/all-that-and-q", "id": 935114, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206412/esr-qi2-magnetic-car-charger-nes-controllers-deal-sale", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "ESR\u2019s inexpensive Qi2 car charger is more than 40 percent off for a limited time", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T12:44:51+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of OpenAI\u2019s logo over a Vergecast illustration.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/0aPMKxBdbsJmxyS_Tmo2wh9T6hU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483602/VST_0726_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"za4Mri\">Google is dying. Google is unstoppable. Somehow, right now, it feels like both of those things are true. For the first time in more than a decade, there appear to be products that might actually threaten Google Search as the centerpiece of the web \u2014 including <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/25/24205701/openai-searchgpt-ai-search-engine-google-perplexity-rival\">OpenAI\u2019s new SearchGPT</a>. And yet Google Search continues to dominate the market and make truly <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204618/google-search-ai-q2-2024-earnings-results\">unfathomable amounts of money</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"THeCly\">On <a href=\"https://link.chtbl.com", "id": 934656, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206582/searchgpt-google-reddit-ai-search-alexa-vergecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The Google era is officially over", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A screenshot showing four feeds of Olympics events.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/8X3c5GgCTOu8RT_bBiAN0t34wj0=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483502/Olympics_on_Peacock_demo_image_Discovery_Multiview.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Peacock\u2019s Multiview is a way to see all the best stuff at the Olympics all at once.</em> | Image: Peacock</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"mlNGRy\">For once, the answer for how to stream sports is simple: if you want to watch the <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Folympics.com%2Fen%2Fparis-2024&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F7%2F26%2F24206108%2Fhow-to-watch-olympics-2024-paris-peacock\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">2024 Paris Olympics</a>, you need only open up Peacock. This is the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2021/8/9/22617399/peacock-olympics-streaming-whats-nex", "id": 934273, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206108/how-to-watch-olympics-2024-paris-peacock", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How to stream the Olympics like a champ", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T11:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/aygm4xKhaGFKcNNZiZoUN58LASU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483481/jtuohy_220222_5043_0005.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Nest Hello video doorbell can now be fully migrated to the Google Home app from the Nest app.</em> | Photo by Jennifer Pattison Tuohy / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"D45FP7\">Google <a href=\"https://www.googlenestcommunity.com/t5/Blog/Public-Preview-updates-Expanded-support-for-Nest-Doorbell-1st-gen-and/ba-p/632891?emcs_t=S2h8ZW1haWx8Ym9hcmRfc3Vic2NyaXB0aW9ufExaMU5BQktDNlFHQVcwfDYzMjg5MXxTVUJTQ1JJUFRJT05TfGhL\">announced this week</a> that it\u2019s rolling out support for its <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2018/5/3/17312166/nest-hello-yale-lock-smart-home-review\">Nest Hello</a> doorbell in the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/10/23717404/google-home-app-release-date-features-matter-io\">Google Home app</a>. This allows you to transfer Goo", "id": 934274, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206371/nest-hello-doorbell-google-home-app-new-features", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google brings Nest Hello support to the Home app", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T10:27:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Vector illustration of the Crowdstrike logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NpUrTkum_WKiSa_b5K2M-Uo3dpw=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483419/STK275_CROWDSTRIKE_CVIRGINIA_B.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hVJosc\">Microsoft is still <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/25/24206112/microsoft-crowdstrike-windows-outage-internal-response-notepad\">helping CrowdStrike clean up the mess</a> that kicked off a week ago when 8.5 million PCs went offline due to a buggy CrowdStrike update. Now, the software giant is calling for changes to Windows, and has dropped some subtle hints that it\u2019s prioritizing making Windows more resilient and willing to push security vendors like CrowdStrike to stop accessing the Windows kernel.</p>\n<p id=\"RoztcL\">While CrowdStrike has <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/24/24205020/crowdstrike-test-software-bug-windows-bsod-issue\">blamed a", "id": 933948, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206719/microsoft-windows-changes-crowdstrike-kernel-driver", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft calls for Windows changes and resilience after CrowdStrike outage", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T10:09:29+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Steam brand logo against a blue and black backdrop\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/oE2wQAA7RuMsEQ6dI9-D77RYiTo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483409/STK138_Stream_Kradtke_02.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bznEhM\">Valve has introduced some changes to Steam that should make it easier to find and install playable game demos. In a <a href=\"https://steamcommunity.com/games/593110/announcements/detail/6233628070477025191\">new events blog post</a>, Steam said the \u201cGreat Steam Demo Update\u201d was based on developer and player feedback, with new functionality that makes demos behave more like standalone games hosted on the platform.</p>\n<p id=\"V0iKW5\">For one, demos can now have a store page that\u2019s completely separate from the main game, allowing developers to display demo-specific content like trailers, screenshots, and supported features. These pages will also display bu", "id": 933949, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206720/steam-game-demos-update-library-store-pages", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Steam is getting some big upgrades for game demos", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-26T09:19:11+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of Microsoft\u2019s Surface Pro with an OLED display.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jkGWaO7Z4H5DTGfKI6_DPCeV9Hg=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73483353/DSCF7738.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Chris Welch / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Bz2dOA\">Microsoft has started testing a new way to access your Android phone from directly within Windows 11\u2019s File Explorer. Windows Insiders are <a href=\"https://blogs.windows.com/windows-insider/2024/07/25/ability-to-access-your-android-phone-in-file-explorer-begins-rolling-out-to-windows-insiders/\">now able to test this new feature</a>, which lets you wirelessly browse through folders and files on your Android phone.</p>\n<p id=\"S2akfg\">The integration in File Explorer means your Android device appears just like a regular USB device on the left-hand side, with the ability to copy or move files between a PC and Android phone, and rename or delete them. It\u2019", "id": 933600, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/26/24206712/microsoft-windows-11-file-explorer-android-phone-feature", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Windows 11 will soon add your Android phone to File Explorer", "user": null, "vote": 0}]